# Tailwind Canonical Utilities

- Arbitrary values like `w-[9rem]`, `min-w-[9rem]`, and `px-[18px]` are valid modern Tailwind syntax. They are not deprecated or "old".
- When a built-in Tailwind utility expresses the same value, prefer the canonical utility instead of `[]`.
- Treat lint suggestions such as `suggestCanonicalClasses` as the default choice unless matching the design truly requires a one-off value.

## Preferred

```svelte
<!-- good -->
<div class="md:min-w-36 md:w-40" />

<!-- avoid when an equivalent utility already exists -->
<div class="md:min-w-36 md:w-40" />
```

## Use `[]` Only When Needed

- Keep arbitrary values only when there is no standard Tailwind scale/token for that value.
- If the value maps cleanly to Tailwind's spacing scale, replace it with the canonical class before finishing the change.
